---
description: Flask API Gateway conventions for LMForge
globs: "api/**"
alwaysApply: false
---
Flask Rules:
- All routes MUST use Blueprints (organized under api/internal/router/router.py).
- Dependency Injection: ALWAYS use Injector modules (see api/modules/).
- Configuration: load from .env, use app.config throughout.
- Responses: always jsonify() with proper HTTP status codes.
- Swagger/OpenAPI: add proper decorators/comments for /docs.
- CORS/CSRF: already configured globally — do not override.
- Never put routes directly in app.py — use blueprints.

JSON Handling:
- Request validation: use Pydantic or Flask-WTF schemas.
- Response serialization: use Pydantic models with .model_dump(mode='json').